# Contributing to azdiff
You can greatly help this project by:

- Reporting a bug
- Discussing the current state of the code
- Submitting a fix
- Proposing new features
- Becoming a maintainer

## We Use [Github Flow](https://docs.github.com/en/get-started/quickstart/github-flow)
That means that All Code Changes Happen Through Pull Requests. We actively welcome your pull requests:

1. Fork the repo and create your branch from `main`.
2. If you've added code, add tests.
3. If you've changed APIs, update the documentation.
4. Ensure the test suite passes.
5. Make sure your code doesn't create warnings by dotnet compiler or SonarCloud.
6. Send the pull request!

## Report bugs using [Github issues](https://github.com/jlucaspains/azdiff/issues)
We use GitHub issues to track public bugs.

## Request enhancements using [Github issues](https://github.com/jlucaspains/azdiff/issues)
We also use GitHub issues to track enhancements.

## Write bug reports with detail, background, and sample code
**Great Bug Reports** tend to have:

- A quick summary and/or background
- Steps to reproduce
  - Be specific!
  - Give sample code if you can.
- What you expected would happen
- What actually happens
- Notes (possibly including why you think this might be happening, or stuff you tried that didn't work)

## Use .NET default Coding Style
The default .NET coding style which is enforced by VS and VS Code should be used.

